The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 January is 167,272 (19,279.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 January, there were 11,068 new confirmed cases (1,275.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 January, there were 12,088 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 8% (1,020 fewer cases).
